crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a sophisticated Remote Access Trojan (RAT) or spyware. It exhibits several high-malicious behaviors: 1) Dynamic API Resolution: It uses a minimal import table (ExitProcess, GetProcAddress, LoadLibraryA) to resolve the majority of its functionality at runtime (sub_40182a), a common technique for evading static analysis. 2) Spyware Capabilities: The function sub_404255 implements a desktop screenshot capture routine, saving the output as a .BMP file and storing metadata in the registry. 3) C2 Communication: Function sub_4031ee handles network exfiltration via HTTP POST requests, utilizing custom Base64 encoding (sub_4012a4) for data obfuscation. 4) System Fingerprinting: It performs detailed OS version checks (sub_401f0f) to tailor its payload. 5) Persistence and Discovery: It includes recursive file system traversal (sub_4067ad) and registry modification capabilities for persistence and data collection.
